text:
@KillerBrig I disagree. The progression feels way better than it used to imo.

Although it COULD use... some building upon.

Framerate is a fairly obvious optimization issue. That's not a valid complaint until the game is actually out, since it's possible they haven't optimized it properly yet.

@BaronCreel
You seem remarkably sure of that. On what grounds? I'd say the distinct lack of radio silence is a pretty good indication that work hasn't stopped.
Plus, they seem savvy enough to want to avoid the backlash the more recent shitheels have gotten for lying and not delivering on promised product, so it's an awful lot of work and risk involved to fake the stuff they put up on the site.

@SupraDarky 
Yeah, I mean, the soundtrack is top notch. It really is. But its been so long since the game has had any worthwhile progress. I let it sit for a few months in my Steam Library and just logged in to check if anything new had been updated. Everything was the same. No noticeable changes.

Meanwhile Terraria is getting close to releasing its 1.3 patch which will add so many new things.

@SupraDarky
They are still working on it, just that development has slowed down to a crawl, it's been in "Early Access" like that for years with little to no advance. However look at it on the other hand, do you know how many years this game has been in development before being released as even a limited beta or early access? Heck even the kickstarter campaign took ages after the initial start of dev to kick in. I still believe there'll be improvement and development however that it will take tremendous amounts of time considering the size of the team that's working on it. To see a "Full release" of this might be a bit too enthusiastic though, but periodic updates will happen and advance will happen.

In any case, stay tuned for "Wanderlust: Adventures" Still by chucklefish (Yeti trunk) with OST by no one other than Chris Christodolou! That one should be released shortly, actually.
